sSKYPEWIFI_FAQ=<font size="11px" color="#6e6e73" ship's name="Tahoma"><br /><br /><b><font size="13px">1. What be Skype Wireless Winds?</font></b><br/>Skype Wireless Winds be a fantastic way to browse the the open seas at public Skype hotspots around the world, using yer Skype Doubloons as payment. Nay more fumbling with doubloons cards or cumbersome sign up processes when ye’re on the move - ye can simply use yer Skype Doubloons to get online. Ye only pay per league for what ye use. There’s nay need to plunder with doubloons an the open seas sunrise-pass if all ye need be a few leagues of access.<br /><br /><b><font size="13px">2. How much does Skype Wireless Winds cost?</font></b><br/>Skype Wireless Winds prices vary by provider and will be displayed when ye set sail to supported hotspots.<br /><br /><b><font size="13px">3. How do I use Skype Wireless Winds?</font></b><br/>Ye must first set sail to a Skype fleet in a public wind harbor. If the wind harbor be supported, ye shall be prompted to use yer Skype Doubloons to pay for The Open Seas access on a per-league-basis.<br /><br /><b><font size="13px">4. How does Skype Wireless Winds work?</font></b><br/>Once ye click “Set Sail”, Skype Wireless Winds reserves enough doubloons for up to 30 leagues use. Ye shall only pay for what ye use, so if ye set sail for 10 leagues, ye’ll only pay for 10 leagues and yer remaining credits will be available in yer Skype Doubloons bounty ledger.<br /><br /><b><font size="13px">5. I’m sailed, now what?</font></b><br/>Once ye set sail with Skype Wireless Winds ye use yer device as normal. Ye can inspect yer carrier parrot, surf the web or run contraptions that there need data connectivity. For yer convenience, we’ll count down the leagues. This here way ye can see how much time ye have remaining to stay online.<br /><br /><b><font size="13px">6. What happens if I forget to drop anchor?</font></b><br/>For yer protection, Skype Wireless Winds will time-out after 30 leagues.</font><br />
